    </thing>
	
<!-- Judgment of the Ten Kings of Hell -->
	<thing
		id="maTenKings"
		name="Judgment of the Ten Kings of Hell"
		compset="Magic"
		isunique="yes"
		description="When confronted by a demon, the exorcist can appeal to the court of the {i}Feng Du{/i} in order to send this cursed soul back to Hell.{br}{br} Facing a creature such as an Emo, a Taotie, a succubus or an evil spirit, the exorcist spends 12 Chi points and carries out an Opposition Test of Earth + Exorcism against the Resistance of the creature, this Test being counted as an action in a combat situation. If he succeeds, he draws the attention of the Kings of Hell to the unjustified presence, in the world of men, of a demon who is at once dragged before the {i}Feng Du{/i}, disappearing from the Earth forever.">
		
		<fieldval field="trtAbbrev" value="10Kg"/>
		<fieldval field="trtUser" value="6"/>
		<fieldval field="maPrep" value="One action"/>
		<fieldval field="maPrepST" value="N/A"/>
		<fieldval field="maDur" value="Instantaneous"/>
		<fieldval field="maArea" value="On sight"/>
		<fieldval field="chiCost" value="12"/>
		<fieldval field="maImprove" value="For each additional 5 Chi points spent when this technique is used, the exorcist increases the result of his Test of Earth + Exorcism by 1."/>
		
		<usesource source="qinLegends"/>

		<tag group="Way" tag="Exorcism"/>
		
		<link linkage="magicskill" thing="skExor"/>
		
		<!-- Uncomment for prerequisites
		<exprreq message="Calligraphy 1+ required."><![CDATA[
			#traitfound[skCall] >= 1
		]]></exprreq>
		-->
    </thing>
	
<!-- Judgment of Heaven -->
	<thing
		id="maJudHvn"
		name="Judgment of Heaven"
		compset="Magic"
		isunique="yes"
		description="Facing a creature not yet corrupted by evil, the exorcist can submit it to the judgment of the gods of the Celestial Court for a ruling on the case.{br}{br} Confronted by a creature like a ghost or a {i}Yao{/i}, the exorcist spends 12 Chi points and carries out an Opposition Test of Earth + Exorcism against the Resistance of the creature, this Test being counted as an action in a combat situation. If the creature, of its own free will, submits itself to the Judgment of Heaven, the Test can be ignored, but the exorcist still spends his Chi.{br}{br} A ghost without any evil intent, brought before the court of the celestial gods, has its curse removed and goes back directly to the Wheel of Reincarnation in order to be quickly reborn. A ghost who has fallen into evil, however, is delivered into the hands of the Judges of Hell and suffers a thousands tortures in the {i}Feng Du{/i} before it can be reincarnated, once purified.{br}{br} A peaceful {i}Yao{/i} submitted to the Judgment of Heaven earns the right to live as a human; it loses all its abilities and all its supernatural powers but its soul becomes fully human, thus making him impervious to the spells and techniques that target creatures and allowing it to integrate into the world of men without fearing, one day, being unmasked and rejected. An evil Yao, on the other hand, regresses and reverts to its original animal shape, losing as a consequence all its abilities and all its supernatural powers. It becomes a simple animal again and has to live the rest of its life as such.">
		
		<fieldval field="trtAbbrev" value="JdHn"/>
		<fieldval field="trtUser" value="6"/>
		<fieldval field="maPrep" value="One action"/>
		<fieldval field="maPrepST" value="N/A"/>
		<fieldval field="maDur" value="Instantaneous"/>
		<fieldval field="maArea" value="On sight"/>
		<fieldval field="chiCost" value="12"/>
		<fieldval field="maImprove" value="For each additional 5 Chi points spent when this technique is used, the exorcist increases the result of his Test of Earth + Exorcism by 1."/>
		
		<usesource source="qinLegends"/>

